{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17586013","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17586013"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:24:02+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:24:02+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15047"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15047","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15047"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.05,0,0,0.86]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7735"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116271"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7735","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7735"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15047"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98267"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8115"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18890"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18894"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116271","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/116271"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAcute kidney injury (AKI) is characterised by a rapid decline in kidney function over hours to days.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is typically observed in acute kidney injury?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Decreased serum potassium levels","Decreased serum phosphate levels","Increased urinary calcium excretion","Increased erythropoietin production","Accumulation of nitrogenous waste products"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAcute kidney injury results in multiple biochemical and physiological derangements due to the rapid loss of renal function. The hallmark feature is the \u003Cstrong\u003Eaccumulation of nitrogenous waste products\u003C/strong\u003E, which manifests as elevated blood urea nitrogen and creatinine levels as the kidneys lose their ability to filter and excrete metabolic waste.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased serum potassium levels\u003C/strong\u003E does not occur in AKI; instead, hyperkalaemia typically develops due to reduced potassium excretion. \u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased serum phosphate levels\u003C/strong\u003E is also incorrect as phosphate retention occurs in AKI, leading to hyperphosphataemia. \u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased urinary calcium excretion\u003C/strong\u003E is not characteristic of AKI, as calcium excretion typically decreases. \u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased erythropoietin production\u003C/strong\u003E does not occur; erythropoietin production actually decreases in AKI, potentially contributing to anaemia. Other features of AKI include metabolic acidosis, fluid overload, and decreased activated vitamin D production.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Acute kidney injury causes retention of phosphate, potassium, and hydrogen ions","Acute kidney injury leads to dysregulation of fluid balance and accumulation of waste products","Acute kidney injury results in decreased production of erythropoietin and activated vitamin D"],"references":["Gaut JP, Liapis H. Acute kidney injury pathology and pathophysiology: a retrospective review. Clin Kidney J. 2020 Oct 10;14(2):526-536. doi: 10.1093/ckj/sfaa142. PMID: 33623675; PMCID: PMC7886540.","Jennette, J. C., \u0026 D\u0027Agati, V. D. (2023). Heptinstall\u0027s Pathology of the Kidney. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98267"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15047"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98267","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/98267"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-28T03:55:09+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T03:55:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7735"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116271"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4933","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4933"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd43","name":"Urinary","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T09:50:28+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"13"}},"heading":{"da